  <h1>LSD (Lysergic Acid Diethylamide) – Complete Synthesis</h1>
  <p class="warning">⚠️ WARNING: This guide is for informational purposes only. Possession, synthesis, or distribution of LSD is illegal in most jurisdictions. Proceed at your own risk. ⚠️</p>

  <h2>1. Precursors & Reagents</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Ergolamine tartrate (or lysergic acid) – primary alkaloid source.</li>
    <li>Diethylamine – nucleophile for amide formation.</li>
    <li>Thionyl chloride (SOCl₂) – activates lysergic acid to acid chloride.</li>
    <li>Triethylamine (TEA) – base for neutralization.</li>
    <li>Dry dichloromethane (DCM) – solvent, anhydrous.</li>
    <li>Ice‑cold sodium bicarbonate solution – work‑up quench.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Equipment</h2>
  <pre>
- 250 mL three‑neck round‑bottom flask
- Magnetic stir bar (PTFE‑coated)
- Addition funnel with nitrogen inlet
- Ice bath with temperature control (0 °C)
- Inert atmosphere setup (argon balloon)
- Vacuum filtration apparatus
- Rotary evaporator (≤ 40 °C water bath)
  </pre>

  <h2>3. Safety Precautions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Wear nitrile gloves, goggles, and a full‑face respirator (P100 filter).</li>
    <li>Perform all steps inside a certified fume hood; never in a residential kitchen.</li>
    <li>Keep all reagents away from open flames; thionyl chloride is highly reactive.</li>
    <li>Dispose of waste according to local hazardous waste regulations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Procedure</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Activation:</strong> Dissolve 10 g of lysergic acid in 100 mL anhydrous DCM under argon. Cool to 0 °C. Add 12 mL thionyl chloride dropwise over 15 min, stirring continuously.</li>
    <li><strong>Amide Formation:</strong> After 30 min, slowly add 12 mL diethylamine (excess) via addition funnel while maintaining 0 °C. Stir for 2 h, allowing the acid chloride to react forming lysergic acid diethylamide.</li>
    <li><strong>Work‑up:</strong> Quench the reaction by adding ice‑cold 200 mL saturated NaHCO₃ solution slowly. Separate the organic layer, wash with brine, dry over anhydrous Na₂SO₄.</li>
    <li><strong>Purification:</strong> Concentrate the organic layer on a rotary evaporator (< 40 °C). Recrystallize the crude product from ethanol‑water (1:1) at 4 °C. Collect crystals via vacuum filtration.</li>
    <li><strong>Final Drying:</strong> Transfer crystals to a desiccator under argon. Store in an amber glass vial with a desiccant pack.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>5. Yield & Storage</h2>
  <p>Typical yield: 30‑45 % pure LSD·HCl (≈ 2‑3 mg per gram of lysergic acid). Store at −20 °C, protected from light.</p>

